org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.neo4j.embedded.dialect.impl

Class EmbeddedNeo4jTupleSnapshot

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.neo4j.embedded.dialect.impl.EmbeddedNeo4jTupleSnapshot
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TupleSnapshot

    public final class EmbeddedNeo4jTupleSnapshot
extends Object
implements TupleSnapshot
    Represents the Tuple snapshot as loaded by the Neo4j datastore.

    The columns of the tuple are mapped as properties of the node.

    Author:
    Davide D'Alto <davide@hibernate.org>

        public boolean isNew()
        Whether this snapshot has been newly created (meaning it doesn't have an actual Node yet) or not. A node will be in the "new" state between the createTuple() call and the next insertOrUpdateTuple() call.
